{"id":45588,"date":"2024-01-17T09:04:00","date_gmt":"2024-01-17T03:34:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=45588"},"modified":"2023-05-18T18:03:13","modified_gmt":"2023-05-18T12:33:13","slug":"11-tv-room-design-ideas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/11-tv-room-design-ideas\/","title":{"rendered":"Big Style for Small Spaces: TV Room Ideas for Limited Spaces"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>Get ready to transform your compact TV room into a cosy and functional retreat that&#8217;s big on style!<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Who says bigger is always better? When creating a TV room in a compact home, sometimes a smaller space can lead to bigger possibilities. With limited square footage, you can get creative and design a relaxing and stylish room. In this blog, we&#8217;ll share our top ideas and tips for designing a small TV room that&#8217;s full of personality and a delight to spend time in.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>From clever storage solutions to chic seating options, get ready to discover how to create a small TV room that packs a big punch! Whether working with a studio apartment, a compact living room, or a tiny den, our small TV room ideas will help you turn even the tiniest of rooms into stylish and functional spaces. So let&#8217;s dive in and discover the possibilities of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/space-saving-design\/\">small space design<\/a>!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Modern TV Room Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Step into a world of cosy sophistication with this modern TV room design! With pastel hues setting the tone, this space invites you to relax and enjoy your favourite TV shows in style. The laser-cut Jaali design behind the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/guides\/different-types-of-tv-units\/\">TV unit<\/a> adds a touch of geometric flair and separates the space from the foyer, giving you a sense of privacy and seclusion. So whether you&#8217;re cuddled up with a loved one or hosting a movie night with friends, this small TV room is the perfect place to unwind and make lasting memories.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205137\/modern-tv-room-design.jpg\" alt=\"Modern TV Room Design with pastel hues setting the tone\" class=\"wp-image-45594\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205137\/modern-tv-room-design.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205137\/modern-tv-room-design-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205137\/modern-tv-room-design-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205137\/modern-tv-room-design-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Choose soothing colours for a relaxing vibe\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">TV Room With Glass Door Partition<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This small but mighty TV room design blends functionality with style in this <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/contemporary-interior-design-ideas\/\">contemporary home<\/a>. An open layout is ideal for compact homes to create a sense of spaciousness. But when you need more privacy, a glass partition like this provides an elegant buffer between the other spaces in your home. The minimalistic wooden TV unit also offers ample space for your electronics and media in the drawers. This allows you to enjoy a chic, uncluttered space that seamlessly blends with the rest of your open-layout home!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205129\/tv-room-with-glass-door-partition.jpg\" alt=\"TV Room With Glass Door Partition that blends functionality with style\" class=\"wp-image-45593\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205129\/tv-room-with-glass-door-partition.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205129\/tv-room-with-glass-door-partition-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205129\/tv-room-with-glass-door-partition-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205129\/tv-room-with-glass-door-partition-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Open layout harmony with a see-through partition<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Small TV Room With Rotating TV Unit<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Don&#8217;t let a small home cramp your style! Although it can be challenging to create an entertainment zone in a studio apartment. We bring you the ultimate solution &#8211; a rotating TV unit. A swivel TV unit offers the best of both worlds as it can be rotated to suit your preference. This means you get to watch TV not just from the sofa but also from the comfort of your bed. Isn&#8217;t that cool? This smart TV unit elevates the style quotient of the compact studio apartment while offering the perfect separation between spaces. Moreover, it has multiple open shelves for books, decor items and other knick-knacks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205123\/small-tv-room-with-rotating-tv-unit.jpg\" alt=\"Small TV Room With Rotating TV Unit that elevates the style quotient\" class=\"wp-image-45592\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205123\/small-tv-room-with-rotating-tv-unit.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205123\/small-tv-room-with-rotating-tv-unit-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205123\/small-tv-room-with-rotating-tv-unit-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205123\/small-tv-room-with-rotating-tv-unit-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Multifunctional furniture for compact TV rooms<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">TV Room Design Under The Stairs<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Instead of looking for a separate space to serve as your TV room, why not simply accommodate an unused area? For instance, the space under the stairs. This small TV room is the ultimate sanctuary if you live in a compact duplex! Because it merges comfort, style, and functionality all in one. With a spacious floating TV unit and a rustic wooden sofa for seating, you get a compact yet trendy space right under the stairs! This small TV room design idea lets you maximise your floor space without sacrificing style. Not just that, it also comes with wardrobes and lots of open shelves that help keep the space well-organised.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205116\/tv-room-design-under-the-stairs.jpg\" alt=\"TV Room Design Under The Stairs for a compact duplex\" class=\"wp-image-45591\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205116\/tv-room-design-under-the-stairs.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205116\/tv-room-design-under-the-stairs-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205116\/tv-room-design-under-the-stairs-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205116\/tv-room-design-under-the-stairs-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Creative way to maximise unused spaces<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Space saving tv units with our innovative home interior solutions\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/07151210\/space-saving-tv-units-with-our-innovative-home-interior-solutions.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Living Room TV Wall Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Add an extra layer of fun to your TV room <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/\">interior design<\/a> with a mini bar tucked away in the corner! This compact yet stylish space is the ultimate entertainment hub, where you can seamlessly transition from enjoying a thrilling match on game days to shaking up refreshing cocktails. With a cushy sofa that invites you to sink in and an uber-cool <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/tv-unit-design-ideas-for-living-room\/\">living room tv wall design<\/a>, get set to impress all your guests. The mini bar also has two bar stools that offer extra seating space. The stylish box cabinet under the TV has open shelves, drawers, and open space at the top to house all your TV room essentials. So why settle for a dull TV room when you can have one that&#8217;s both funky and fabulous?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205110\/living-room-tv-wall-design.jpg\" alt=\"Living room TV wall design to unwind and indulge\" class=\"wp-image-45590\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205110\/living-room-tv-wall-design.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205110\/living-room-tv-wall-design-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205110\/living-room-tv-wall-design-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205110\/living-room-tv-wall-design-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>An entertainment haven to unwind and indulge<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">TV Panel Design For Living Room<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re creating an entertainment area in your living room, a bold TV panel design like this is sure to make a statement. This innovative living room TV wall design transports you to a world of entertainment without taking up too much floor space. The vibrant TV room furniture infuses personality and adds a burst of energy to the small TV room. The pop of yellow creates a striking contrast against the grey brick wall, while the rich wooden panels add a warm accent. We love the addition of floating open box shelves on the brick wall for displaying books and decor items.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205103\/tv-panel-design-for-living-room.jpg\" alt=\"TV Panel Design For Living Room that uses playful colours\" class=\"wp-image-45589\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205103\/tv-panel-design-for-living-room.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205103\/tv-panel-design-for-living-room-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205103\/tv-panel-design-for-living-room-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/17205103\/tv-panel-design-for-living-room-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Use playful colours for a captivating design<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, there are endless possibilities to make your simple TV room a standout feature in your home. Whether you&#8217;re binge-watching your favourite show or entertaining guests, we hope these small design ideas will inspire you to create a charming corner in your home. For more <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/\">home interior design ideas<\/a>, don&#8217;t hesitate to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/contact-us\/\">get in touch<\/a> with our expert designers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FAQs On TV Room Ideas<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How can I decorate my TV room to make it more inviting?<\/strong><br>Decorate your TV room with comfortable chairs or a sofa with plush cushions and throw pillows inviting you to relax. Use soft lighting to create a warm and inviting atmosphere, and hang some artwork on the walls to infuse personality into your TV room.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What are some lighting options for a TV room?<\/strong><br>Ambient lights with a dimmer switch are the best option for TV room lighting. Wall sconces can be a stylish and space-saving option for providing ambient lighting in a TV room. You can add table or <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/floor-lamp-ideas\/\">floor lamps<\/a> for more intimate lighting and pendant lights for a modern touch.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How can I make my TV room feel more luxurious?<\/strong><br>You can make your TV room feel more luxurious by using plush fabrics like velvet and faux fur for your upholstery, curtains, and throw pillows. Invest in high-quality seating that&#8217;s comfortable and stylish. Incorporate metallic accents such as gold or silver in your lighting fixtures, hardware, or decor items like vases or picture frames. Use statement art pieces and paintings for a touch of glamour.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How can I incorporate storage into my TV room design?<\/strong><br>An entertainment or TV unit with shelves, cabinets and drawers can be a great way to incorporate storage and keep all your electronics neatly organised. Install wall-mounted cabinets and floating shelves above or around your TV to store books or display decorative items. Opt for an ottoman with hidden storage to add extra seating and storage to your TV room.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What types of seating should I consider for my TV room?<br><\/strong>A sectional sofa is a great option for a larger TV room, while a loveseat is better for small TV rooms. An accent chair with comfortable cushions that complements your sofa can add extra seating space. Alternatively, bean bag chairs are a fun and casual seating option for a TV room.<\/p>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart solutions<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-search=\"Infinity\">\n               \n                <option value=\"+01\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06163948\/01.png\">\n                    +01\n      